  "cooking_instructions": [
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Preheat the oven to 220°C/ 200°C (fan)/ gas 7, then take your <strong>steak </strong>out of the fridge, open the packet and let it adjust to room temperature</p><p>Chop your <strong>potatoes</strong> (skins on) into large bite-sized pieces</p><p>Peel and finely chop (or grate) your <strong>garlic</strong></p>",
      "order": 1,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/2127.-step-1-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/2127.-step-1-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/2127.-step-1-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/2127.-step-1-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/2127.-step-1-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Add the<strong> chopped potatoes</strong> to a baking tray (or two!) with a drizzle of<strong> vegetable oil</strong> and a pinch of <strong>salt</strong> and give everything a good mix up</p><p>Add your <strong>portobello mushroom[s]</strong> to the tray[s]</p><p>Top the <strong>mushroom[s] </strong>with <strong>half</strong> of the<strong> chopped garlic </strong>(you’ll use the rest later!), a knob of <strong>butter</strong> and pinch of <strong>salt</strong>, then drizzle your <strong>Chinese rice wine </strong>evenly over the top</p>",
      "order": 2,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/2127.-step-2-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/2127.-step-2-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/2127.-step-2-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/2127.-step-2-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/2127.-step-2-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Put the tray[s] in the oven for 20-25 min or until the mushroom is tender and the potatoes are starting to crisp</p><p>Meanwhile, combine your <strong>panko breadcrumbs</strong> with a drizzle of <strong>vegetable oil</strong> and a pinch of <strong>salt</strong></p><p>Pat your <strong>rump steak[s] </strong>dry with kitchen paper, then drizzle with <strong>vegetable oil </strong>and season with a generous pinch of <strong>salt</strong> on both sides</p>",
      "order": 3,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/2127.-step-3-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/2127.-step-3-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/2127.-step-3-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/2127.-step-3-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/2127.-step-3-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Heat a large, wide-based pan (preferably non-stick) over a high heat and once very hot add the<strong> seasoned steak</strong></p><p>For rare, cook for 2 min max on each side; for medium-rare, cook for 2-3 min on each side; for medium, cook for 3-4 min on each side</p><p>Tip: Don’t be tempted to move the steak around too much in the pan – this will stop it from browning</p>",
      "order": 4,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/2127.-step-4-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/2127.-step-4-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/2127.-step-4-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/2127.-step-4-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/2127.-step-4-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Once done, transfer the <strong>cooked</strong> <strong>steak</strong> to a plate to rest and reserve the pan with any cooking juices</p><p>Once the potatoes are starting to crisp, add your <strong>cherry tomatoes</strong> to the tray[s], then top the mushroom[s] with the <strong>breadcrumbs</strong></p><p>Return everything to the oven and cook for a further 6-8 min or until the breadcrumbs are golden and the cherry tomatoes are starting to burst – this is your <strong>garlic portobello</strong>,<strong> crispy</strong> <strong>potatoes </strong>and <strong>roasted cherry tomatoes</strong></p>",
      "order": 5,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/2127.-step-5-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/2127.-step-5-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/2127.-step-5-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/2127.-step-5-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/2127.-step-5-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>While the vegetables are roasting, heat a separate, large, wide-based pan with a drizzle of <strong>vegetable oil</strong> and a small knob of <strong>butter</strong></p><p>Wash your <strong>spinach</strong>, then pat dry with<strong> </strong>kitchen paper</p><p>Once hot, remove the pan from the heat, then add the <strong>spinach</strong>, return the pan to the heat and add your<strong> remaining chopped garlic</strong> with a pinch of <strong>salt</strong> and cook for 2-3 min or until wilted – this is your <strong>buttery spinach</strong></p>",
      "order": 6,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/2127.-step-6-1-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
